Tenemos que nos queda una cantidad finita de tiempo en estas posiciones. Vamos a luchar juntos hasta nuestro último minuto en el cargo, para asegurar el futuro de la Florida para todas y cada una de sus familias.

Estoy orgulloso del trabajo que hemos logrado juntos para asegurar el futuro de la Florida creando un ambiente donde los floridanos de todas las edades tienen las herramientas que necesitan para tener éxito en nuestro estado. Pero nuestro trabajo no ha concluido.
El pueblo de Venezuela merece libertad y democracia. Estoy luchando por legislación que impida a las agencias estatales invertir en cualquier compañía que haga negocios con el régimen de Maduro.

No creo que nadie haya podido predecir la tormenta monumental en que se convirtió el Huracán Irma. Pero los floridanos decidimos unirnos y enfrentarlo todos juntos. La respuesta y la solidaridad que demostró nuestro estado me hicieron sentir muy orgulloso de ser Gobernador.

Yo quiero que en el 2018 los votantes de la Florida aprueben una enmienda constitucional haga más difícil a los políticos aumentar los impuestos. Por lo menos dos tercios de la legislatura tendrán que votar a favor de un incremento de impuestos para que se convierta en ley.

Hemos creado un ambiente donde el sector privado agregó casi 1.5 millones de empleos, el PIB creció 26%, el valor de las viviendas se disparó, la deuda estatal se redujo en $9 mil millones, y la tasa de desempleo bajó de más de 10%, al nivel más bajo en 10 años, de apenas 3.6%.

En el 2010, cuando fui candidato a Gobernador, prometí cambiar el statu-quo y crear un ambiente donde las empresas pudieran tener éxito y crear empleos para las familias de la Florida, y los resultados hablan por sí mismos.
We have a finite amount of time left in these positions. Let’s all fight together until our last minute in office to secure Florida’s future for each and every family.
I am proud of the work we have accomplished together to secure Florida’s future by creating an environment where Floridians of all ages have the tools they need to succeed. But, our work is not done.
The people of Venezuela deserve freedom and democracy. I am fighting for legislation that blocks state agencies from investing in any company doing business with the Maduro regime.
Since 2013, I have awarded nearly 13,000 Florida veterans with the Governor’s Veterans Service Award.
Since 2011, 20,000 children in foster care have been adopted.

Overcoming addiction requires incredible strength and bravery and we must make sure that resources are available to help people get the treatment they need. This year, I have proposed to invest $53 million to fight opioid abuse in Florida.

I encourage the Legislature to pass a bill that protects state employees who witness their colleagues being harassed or victimized. I want to ensure the identities of these brave individuals are protected so they feel encouraged to participate in investigations.

No one in Florida who has been a victim of crime should feel ashamed. Victims of crime or harassment deserve to have their voices heard. Last year, we took a step forward to protect those in state government who were victimized. But it is clear that more must be done.

I am also proud to support a measure that is going through the Constitution Revision Commission to give free tuition to the families of fallen first responders, state law enforcement officers and military members who have lost their lives in the line of duty.
Our law enforcement have done an incredible job protecting Florida families and I hope the Legislature will support my proposed pay raise of $30 million for all state sworn officers this year.

I saw firsthand the devastation on the island and I have tried to help the people of Puerto Rico any way I could... and my goal is that Florida be the most welcoming place for people displaced by Hurricane Maria.

I don't think anyone could have predicted the mammoth storm Hurricane Irma would become. But, Floridians came together and faced Hurricane Irma head on. The response and solidarity that was shown by our state was one of the proudest moments that I have had as Governor.
Also, my tax cut package this year will truly benefit every single Floridian- it includes reducing driver's license fees and hurricane preparedness sales tax holidays.

I want 2018 to be the year that Florida voters pass a constitutional amendment that makes it harder for politicians to raise taxes. My proposal would require 2/3rds of the legislature to vote on a tax increase for it to become law.

We’ve created an environment where our private sector has added nearly 1.5 million jobs, our GDP has grown 26%, home values have skyrocketed, we’ve decreased state debt by $9 billion, and our unemployment rate has dropped to a 10-year low of 3.6%.

In 2010, when I ran for Governor, I promised to change the status quo and create an environment where businesses can succeed and create jobs for Florida families, and the results speak for themselves.
I stand here today, at the beginning of my last year as Governor, thankful for the opportunity that we have all had to help our beloved State of Florida.
Honored to deliver my final State of the State today. Tune into the @floridachannel at 11AM!
